#SRC: https://linuxize.com/post/how-to-create-users-in-linux-using-the-useradd-command/

# Change sudo password
> set a password for root user in a single go:
sudo passwd root
> Test it your root password by typing the following command:
su -

# Add user 
sudo useradd flutura
sudo useradd -m flutura (also creates dir)
sudo passwd flutura

# Switch User
su flutura
